\sum_{n=1}^\infty (-1)^{n-1}\frac1n
\displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{(-1)^n}{\frac1n}=\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}(-1)^nn
\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}(-1)^n\frac1n
n=1,3,5,\dots
n=2,4,6,\dots
\,k,m\in\Bbb R\,
\sum_{n=1}^\infty\left(\frac{1}{kn}-\frac{1}{mn}\right)=\frac{m-k}{mk}\sum_{n=1}^\infty\frac{1}{n}\,\,\,\text{diverges}
